  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "Will going for Mtech in CSE in IIT/NIT make a difference to my coding skills?",
  "response": "Pursuing an M.Tech in Computer Science and Engineering (CSE) at a prestigious institution like IIT or NIT can have several benefits that may indirectly enhance your coding skills. Here are some factors to consider:\n\n1. **Curriculum Exposure**: The curriculum in M.Tech programs often includes advanced topics in algorithms, data structures, software engineering, and specialized areas like machine learning, artificial intelligence, or cybersecurity. This theoretical knowledge can deepen your understanding of coding concepts.\n\n2. **Project Work**: M.Tech programs typically involve significant project work, which requires applying coding skills to solve complex problems. This hands-on experience can improve your coding abilities as you work on real-world applications.\n\n3. **Collaboration and Networking**: Studying in a competitive environment with peers who are equally passionate about coding can provide opportunities for collaboration, knowledge sharing, and peer learning, which can enhance your skills.\n\n4. **Research Opportunities**: If you engage in research during your M.Tech, you may work on cutting-edge technologies and coding practices, which can sharpen your skills further. Research often requires problem-solving and coding to implement new ideas.\n\n5. **Mentorship**: Access to experienced faculty and industry professionals can provide valuable insights and guidance, helping you to improve your coding skills and adopt best practices.\n\n6. **Internships and Industry Exposure**: Many M.Tech programs have tie-ups with industries, leading to internships that can provide practical coding experience and exposure to real-world software development processes.\n\n7. **Peer Learning**: Engaging with fellow students who may have different skill sets can help you learn new programming languages, frameworks, and approaches to coding.\n\nHowever, it's important to note that the improvement of coding skills ultimately depends on your personal commitment and effort. If you are proactive in seeking out coding challenges, participating in coding competitions, or working on personal projects, you can significantly enhance your skills regardless of your educational background.",
